Guided Exercise Summary: Project and Cluster Quotas (OpenShift)
1️⃣ Purpose of the Exercise
This exercise demonstrates how resource usage in one namespace can affect the entire cluster and how ResourceQuota prevents a 
namespace from consuming excessive resources.
________________________________________
1. Initial Scenario (Without Quotas)
A deployment test is created that requests 1 CPU per pod.
oc create deployment test --image=hello-world-nginx
oc set resources deployment test --requests=cpu=1
When scaled to 8 replicas:
oc scale deployment test --replicas=8
Only 2 pods run, while others remain Pending because the cluster has insufficient CPU.
Error example:
FailedScheduling: Insufficient cpu
________________________________________
2. Impact on Other Namespaces
Because the selfservice-quotas project consumed most CPU, another namespace (test) cannot create pods requesting 1 CPU.
This shows:
👉 One namespace can block resources for others if no quotas exist.
________________________________________
3. Fix: Create ResourceQuota
Administrator creates a quota:
oc create quota one-cpu --hard=requests.cpu=1
This quota means:
Maximum CPU requests in this namespace = 1 CPU
Quota YAML example:
spec:
  hard:
    requests.cpu: "1"
________________________________________
4. Effects of ResourceQuota
Case 1: Scaling deployment
If test deployment tries to scale to 8 replicas:
❌ Not allowed
Error:
exceeded quota: one-cpu
________________________________________
Case 2: Deployment without CPU request
A new deployment test-2 is created without CPU request.
❌ Pods are not created.
Error:
must specify requests.cpu
Because quota requires CPU requests to be specified.
________________________________________
5. Other Namespaces Still Work
Another project test is created.
Deployment test-3 requesting CPU:
oc set resources deployment test-3 --requests=cpu=1
✅ Pod runs successfully.
This proves:
👉 ResourceQuota only affects the namespace where it is applied.
________________________________________
6. Key Concepts Learned
ResourceQuota
Limits the total resources a namespace can use.
Example:
requests.cpu=1
memory=2Gi
pods=10
________________________________________
Benefits
ResourceQuota helps to:
✔ Prevent a namespace from consuming all cluster resources
✔ Protect other projects in the cluster
✔ Enforce fair resource usage
________________________________________
7. Important Commands
Login
oc login -u developer -p developer
Create project
oc new-project selfservice-quotas
Create deployment
oc create deployment test --image=image-name
Request CPU
oc set resources deployment test --requests=cpu=1
Scale deployment
oc scale deployment test --replicas=8
Create quota
oc create quota one-cpu --hard=requests.cpu=1
View quota
oc get quota one-cpu -o yaml
Check events
oc get events --sort-by .metadata.creationTimestamp
________________________________________
8. Final Conclusion
Without quotas:
•	One project can consume all cluster resources.
With quotas:
•	Each namespace has controlled resource limits.
•	Other namespaces remain unaffected.











